Dog Breed prepared by¶

@zx, Aida Z. and Julian O.¶

Use the dog breed dataset : https://www.kaggle.com/c/dog-breed-identification

Create a notebook containing the following analysis:

  • Check / adjust data quality
  • Extract features from images
  • Reduce dimensionality
  • Classify dogs per breeds
  • Once you are done with these 4 points, use a CNN instead and compare results with your previous solution.

Submit your notebook in HTML format.

# convert jpg files into pixel arrays and store them in dataframe
df_pixels = pd.DataFrame(columns=['id', 'breed', 'pixels'])
for i in range(df_labels.shape[0]):
    img = Image.open(df_labels['path'].iloc[i])
    img = img.resize((64, 64))
    img = np.array(img)
    img = img.flatten()
    df_pixels = pd.concat([df_pixels, pd.DataFrame([[df_labels['id'].iloc[i], df_labels['breed'].iloc[i], img]], columns=['id', 'breed', 'pixels'])], ignore_index=True)

In [123]:
features_df = final_df[["id","breed"]]

features_df["kp"] = None
features_df["des"] = None

for i in range(len(final_df)):


    img = cv2.imread('./data/train/'+features_df.iloc[i, 0]+'.jpg')
    img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
    kp, des = orb.detectAndCompute(img, None)

    features_df.xs(i)["kp"]= kp
    features_df.xs(i)["des"]= des

bf = cv2.BFMatcher_create(cv2.NORM_HAMMING,crossCheck=True)

The script will repeatedly add each new image to the current data frame (x feature) by iterating over the train folder.

In [96]:
x_feature = []
y_feature = []

i = 0 # initialisation
for f, img, path in tqdm(df_labels.values): # f for format ,jpg
    train_img = cv2.imread('./data/train/{}.jpg'.format(f),0)
    label = df_encoded_labels[i]
    train_img_resize = cv2.resize(train_img, (img_rows, img_cols)) 
    x_feature.append(train_img_resize)
    y_feature.append(label)
    i += 1
